{
  "texts": [
    "[58] compare (1) transferring parameters from a source dataset to a target dataset against (2) training one model with two datasets in the non-academic domain.",
    "They demonstrate that semantically related tasks improve while unrelated tasks degrade the performance of the target tasks.",
    "Semwal et al. [74] investigate the extent of task relatedness for product reviews and sentiment classification with sequential transfer learning.",
    "Su et al. [78] study multi-task learning for sentiment classification in product reviews from multiple domains.",
    "Lauscher et al. [50] evaluate multi-task learning on scientific texts but only on one dataset with different annotation layers."
  ]
}